1
00:00:01,084 --> 00:00:02,544
[Marcus] <i>The ones who abducted</i>
<i>Datu Rahman,</i>

2
00:00:02,627 --> 00:00:04,629
<i>they definitely have people inside here.</i>

3
00:00:04,713 --> 00:00:06,005
Everything happened so fast.

4
00:00:06,089 --> 00:00:07,841
They always know our movements.

5
00:00:08,550 --> 00:00:10,385
[man] <i>But even if they sensed our arrival,</i>

6
00:00:10,468 --> 00:00:14,889
<i>how did they manage to get Datu Rahman out</i>
<i>that quickly and that clean?</i>

7
00:00:17,350 --> 00:00:19,978
[reporter] <i>Sir, is there any update</i>
<i>on Datu Rahman's whereabouts?</i>

8
00:00:20,061 --> 00:00:22,105
<i>And was he really taken by the syndicate?</i>

9
00:00:22,188 --> 00:00:26,693
[Jamilah] <i>Agent Marcus Reyes,</i>
<i>you'll pay for what you did to us.</i>

10
00:00:27,193 --> 00:00:30,780
I need an update on your progress
in finding Datu Rahman.

11
00:00:30,864 --> 00:00:33,158
As of now, all of my leads are dead.

12
00:00:33,241 --> 00:00:34,367
[key clacks on floor]

13
00:00:34,451 --> 00:00:36,036
- [Lara] My keys.
- [Marcus] I got it.

14
00:00:37,120 --> 00:00:39,748
What's that? Why is there
a GPS tracker in my car?

15
00:00:39,831 --> 00:00:41,291
We need to be careful.

16
00:00:41,374 --> 00:00:43,209
We don't know who our enemy is.

17
00:00:43,293 --> 00:00:45,128
Sir! Have you heard?

18
00:00:45,211 --> 00:00:47,297
[Felix] <i>Condencido and Vinluan</i>
<i>were gunned down</i>

19
00:00:47,380 --> 00:00:48,798
<i>last night while on patrol.</i>

20
00:00:48,882 --> 00:00:51,551
<i>This is scary. We're in danger.</i>
<i>We need to be careful.</i>

21
00:00:51,634 --> 00:00:55,346
Wasn't there a CCTV camera on the street
where Condencido and Vinluan were shot?

22
00:00:55,430 --> 00:00:58,767
The footage is corrupted,
including the backup files.

23
00:00:58,850 --> 00:01:01,186
- How did that happen?
- We don't know either, sir.

24
00:01:04,272 --> 00:01:05,565
[Jalil] <i>Rashid, what are you going to do?</i>

25
00:01:05,648 --> 00:01:06,483
[Rashid] Jalil?

26
00:01:07,067 --> 00:01:09,235
Just ignore it. It'll only cause trouble.

27
00:01:09,319 --> 00:01:10,445
Do you know Zylverix?

28
00:01:10,528 --> 00:01:14,824
I saw the police who raided our place
with Marcus Reyes.

29
00:01:14,908 --> 00:01:16,659
- [tires screeching]
<i>- There were cars going in and out.</i>

30
00:01:16,743 --> 00:01:19,287
<i>I don't know if this is</i>
<i>related to your father,</i>

31
00:01:19,370 --> 00:01:21,748
<i>but I thought it might help you.</i>

32
00:01:24,042 --> 00:01:26,836
Are you also looking for Father here?

33
00:01:30,256 --> 00:01:36,930
[mysterious theme music playing]

34
00:01:46,981 --> 00:01:47,941
[in Arabic] Peace be upon you.

35
00:01:48,024 --> 00:01:49,234
And peace be upon you.

36
00:01:49,317 --> 00:01:53,154
I saw Marcus Reyes
surveilling outside Zylverix.

37
00:01:53,238 --> 00:01:55,907
I knew something was hidden there.

38
00:01:55,990 --> 00:01:58,118
And I need to find out what it is.

39
00:01:58,952 --> 00:02:00,453
But the place is too big.

40
00:02:00,537 --> 00:02:02,413
Don't worry. I'll help you.

41
00:02:02,497 --> 00:02:04,332
I'll help you search the place.

42
00:02:04,916 --> 00:02:06,167
It's on my route anyway.

43
00:02:07,252 --> 00:02:08,128
[in Tausug] Thank you.

44
00:02:13,258 --> 00:02:15,510
[reporter] <i>At midnight last night,</i>

45
00:02:15,593 --> 00:02:19,973
<i>police officers PO3 Condencido</i>
<i>and PO3 Vinluan were shot while on patrol.</i>

46
00:02:20,056 --> 00:02:22,308
<i>The incident is said</i>
<i>to be a random attack,</i>

47
00:02:22,392 --> 00:02:26,938
<i>but there's still no clear evidence</i>
<i>on who's behind it.</i>

48
00:02:27,021 --> 00:02:29,941
I think it was intentional.

49
00:02:30,024 --> 00:02:33,194
[reporter] <i>The families and friends</i>
<i>of the victims</i>

50
00:02:33,278 --> 00:02:34,612
<i>are now calling for justice.</i>

51
00:02:34,696 --> 00:02:35,780
- [Usman] Sir.
- [sinister music playing]

52
00:02:36,573 --> 00:02:38,241
I spoke with Buster earlier.

53
00:02:38,992 --> 00:02:42,620
I found out all CCTV footage
from the time of the incident

54
00:02:42,704 --> 00:02:44,706
was wiped out.

55
00:02:45,373 --> 00:02:48,167
Do you think that's just a coincidence?

56
00:02:49,294 --> 00:02:50,879
Everything's been erased.

57
00:02:53,047 --> 00:02:55,091
There's no way that was all a coincidence.

58
00:02:57,802 --> 00:02:59,053
That's what I'm thinking too.

59
00:03:00,680 --> 00:03:03,433
I knew Vinluan and Condencido.

60
00:03:03,975 --> 00:03:05,727
They were hardworking officers.

61
00:03:06,394 --> 00:03:07,395
And they had no enemies.

62
00:03:07,478 --> 00:03:11,107
[pensive music playing]

63
00:03:11,774 --> 00:03:12,901
You're right.

64
00:03:14,903 --> 00:03:16,613
It wasn't just an accident.

65
00:03:21,117 --> 00:03:23,536
[Marcus] <i>Does this building</i>
<i>have a hidden exit?</i>

66
00:03:25,330 --> 00:03:27,206
<i>Where did they take Datu Rahman out?</i>

67
00:03:27,290 --> 00:03:28,875
<i>How did they outsmart us?</i>

68
00:03:31,628 --> 00:03:33,421
[line ringing]

69
00:03:33,504 --> 00:03:37,634
Please check all vehicle movements
at the Zylverix Limited Building.

70
00:03:37,717 --> 00:03:39,677
I'll send you the date and time frame.

71
00:03:41,221 --> 00:03:42,430
[sighs]

72
00:03:42,972 --> 00:03:43,890
[knock on door]

73
00:03:44,766 --> 00:03:45,600
[man] Sir.

74
00:03:49,729 --> 00:03:50,772
Thank you.

75
00:03:56,277 --> 00:04:01,574
[tense music playing]

76
00:04:02,492 --> 00:04:05,119
[Lara] <i>What are you up to, Marcus?</i>

77
00:04:05,620 --> 00:04:06,454
‪[dramatic music]

78
00:04:13,836 --> 00:04:15,046
That's it, sir.

79
00:04:15,129 --> 00:04:17,048
Aside from your fellow officers,

80
00:04:17,131 --> 00:04:22,136
no one else entered or exited Zylverix
within that 24-hour window.

81
00:04:26,849 --> 00:04:29,686
I also checked the previous days.
There's really nothing, sir.

82
00:04:30,228 --> 00:04:33,398
Are you sure you checked all the CCTV
covering the compound?

83
00:04:33,481 --> 00:04:34,983
Of course, sir.

84
00:04:35,066 --> 00:04:37,110
Everything. Over and over.
There's really nothing.

85
00:04:37,735 --> 00:04:40,446
Sir, what's really in there?

86
00:04:40,530 --> 00:04:42,657
It looks like only rats are living there.

87
00:04:45,827 --> 00:04:50,206
[Marcus] <i>If no one came in or out</i>

88
00:04:50,915 --> 00:04:54,002
<i>before and after Usman and I arrived,</i>

89
00:04:54,585 --> 00:04:58,673
<i>that means it's possible he wasn't moved.</i>

90
00:04:59,215 --> 00:05:00,591
<i>He's still there.</i>

91
00:05:01,384 --> 00:05:03,219
<i>Datu Rahman wasn't taken out.</i>

92
00:05:04,053 --> 00:05:06,306
<i>We were just searching in the wrong place.</i>

93
00:05:10,310 --> 00:05:15,523
[stirring music playing]

94
00:05:32,749 --> 00:05:35,001
[Marcus] <i>What's the history of Zylverix?</i>

95
00:05:36,335 --> 00:05:37,962
<i>Who owns it?</i>

96
00:05:42,717 --> 00:05:47,889
[pensive music playing]

97
00:05:49,766 --> 00:05:51,642
<i>A shell company?</i>

98
00:05:52,769 --> 00:05:54,437
<i>Why is the building still intact</i>

99
00:05:54,520 --> 00:05:57,398
<i>if no one's using it</i>
<i>and it has no legal owner?</i>

100
00:06:00,693 --> 00:06:01,694
[Marcus] Clear!

101
00:06:26,344 --> 00:06:27,553
[Marcus] <i>He's not here.</i>

102
00:06:29,097 --> 00:06:30,515
<i>Not here either.</i>

103
00:06:38,314 --> 00:06:39,565
[exhales]

104
00:06:40,108 --> 00:06:42,443
[Marcus] <i>Where are you, Datu Rahman?</i>

105
00:06:44,195 --> 00:06:46,489
[reporter] <i>At midnight last night,</i>

106
00:06:46,572 --> 00:06:51,828
<i>police officers PO3 Condencido</i>
<i>and PO3 Vinluan were shot while on patrol.</i>

107
00:06:51,911 --> 00:06:53,996
<i>The incident is said</i>
<i>to be a random attack,</i>

108
00:06:54,080 --> 00:06:58,668
<i>but there's still no clear evidence</i>
<i>on who's behind it…</i>

109
00:06:58,751 --> 00:07:00,461
- Sir!
- Reyes?

110
00:07:00,545 --> 00:07:03,506
- <i>…are now calling for justice.</i>
- Sir.

111
00:07:03,589 --> 00:07:05,800
We need to lock down
the Zylverix Building.

112
00:07:06,509 --> 00:07:09,846
- What? Why? You've already been there!
- [tense music playing]

113
00:07:09,929 --> 00:07:12,181
Sir, we made a slight miscalculation.

114
00:07:13,182 --> 00:07:16,018
But I think Datu Rahman
hasn't been taken out.

115
00:07:16,102 --> 00:07:17,687
They're still hiding him there.

116
00:07:19,021 --> 00:07:20,148
Perfect timing.

117
00:07:20,773 --> 00:07:23,151
We're being criticized
by the media right now

118
00:07:23,234 --> 00:07:26,821
over the deaths of Condencido and Vinluan.

119
00:07:27,405 --> 00:07:28,823
[in English] We need a win!

120
00:07:29,407 --> 00:07:30,575
[in English] Yes, sir.

121
00:07:31,451 --> 00:07:34,537
[stirring music playing]

122
00:07:34,620 --> 00:07:36,205
[line ringing]

123
00:07:36,289 --> 00:07:39,625
Usman, we're heading back
to the Zylverix building.

124
00:07:40,668 --> 00:07:42,628
Go on ahead. I'll catch up to you.

125
00:07:42,712 --> 00:07:45,590
[suspenseful music playing]

126
00:07:45,673 --> 00:07:52,555
[police siren wailing]

127
00:07:57,143 --> 00:07:58,227
[policeman 1] Sir.

128
00:07:58,936 --> 00:07:59,854
Carry on.

129
00:07:59,937 --> 00:08:06,527
[foreboding music playing]

130
00:08:06,611 --> 00:08:11,532
This is a full-scale search
for Datu Rahman!

131
00:08:12,700 --> 00:08:14,243
Seal all exits.

132
00:08:15,036 --> 00:08:16,871
Lockdown the whole perimeter.

133
00:08:17,788 --> 00:08:19,749
If he really is in there,

134
00:08:20,416 --> 00:08:23,794
you better make sure
that he won't get through us.

135
00:08:23,878 --> 00:08:25,046
Understood?!

136
00:08:25,129 --> 00:08:26,214
[all] Yes, sir!

137
00:08:26,297 --> 00:08:27,590
[in English] Alright!

138
00:08:27,673 --> 00:08:31,010
Unit 1, secure the perimeter
and the lobby.

139
00:08:31,093 --> 00:08:33,846
Unit 2, take the second floor.

140
00:08:34,347 --> 00:08:36,974
Unit 3, take the third floor.

141
00:08:37,058 --> 00:08:39,560
Remaining units,
take the rest of the floors.

142
00:08:39,644 --> 00:08:40,478
Move!

143
00:08:41,145 --> 00:08:42,146
[Felix] Move!

144
00:08:42,230 --> 00:08:47,360
[tense music playing]

145
00:08:57,995 --> 00:09:00,665
Usman, you and your men stay here.

146
00:09:00,748 --> 00:09:01,832
Secure this perimeter.

147
00:09:02,458 --> 00:09:03,376
Yes, ma'am.

148
00:09:03,459 --> 00:09:09,924
[suspenseful music playing]

149
00:09:19,183 --> 00:09:20,726
[Jalil] <i>My hunch is right.</i>

150
00:09:21,727 --> 00:09:24,647
<i>They also believe that Father</i>
<i>is still possibly in here.</i>

151
00:09:30,736 --> 00:09:32,405
[door creaks open]

152
00:09:33,698 --> 00:09:34,865
[foot stomps]

153
00:09:34,949 --> 00:09:41,080
[suspenseful music continues]

154
00:09:47,336 --> 00:09:49,255
[in English] Suarez,
Domingo, check that area.

155
00:09:54,969 --> 00:09:55,970
[Felix, in English] Clear!

156
00:10:03,561 --> 00:10:07,231
Angeles, Reyes, take care of this area.

157
00:10:07,315 --> 00:10:08,357
We'll head on to the second floor.

158
00:10:08,441 --> 00:10:09,358
[in English] Yes, sir.

159
00:10:09,859 --> 00:10:10,943
[man] Chief.

160
00:10:15,489 --> 00:10:16,741
Reyes, let's go.

161
00:10:16,824 --> 00:10:23,497
[suspenseful music continues]

162
00:10:28,669 --> 00:10:30,963
Men, have you checked
that corner over there?

163
00:10:31,047 --> 00:10:32,506
Check that area.

164
00:10:51,651 --> 00:10:54,820
[officer] Sir Marcus,
it's negative on the other wing.

165
00:10:54,904 --> 00:10:56,906
Unit 1 has also cleared
the storage already.

166
00:10:56,989 --> 00:10:58,532
- Looks like it's a cold lead.
- No.

167
00:10:59,033 --> 00:11:02,078
Search the entire area.
Including the ventilation.

168
00:11:02,161 --> 00:11:02,995
[in English] Copy.

169
00:11:03,079 --> 00:11:05,331
How about you, sir? Seen anything?

170
00:11:07,249 --> 00:11:08,793
[Lara] Looks like everyone's here.

171
00:11:08,876 --> 00:11:11,629
Director Azuelo is upstairs
on the second floor.

172
00:11:11,712 --> 00:11:12,963
They might be looking for us. Let's go.

173
00:11:13,839 --> 00:11:14,840
[whispers] Okay.

174
00:11:14,924 --> 00:11:20,846
[suspenseful music continues]

175
00:12:06,475 --> 00:12:09,103
Oh? Got anything?

176
00:12:09,186 --> 00:12:11,814
Negative, sir. We didn't find the target.

177
00:12:11,897 --> 00:12:14,483
[Felix clicks tongue] Aye yay yay!

178
00:12:14,567 --> 00:12:15,860
[Azuelo clicks tongue, sighs]

179
00:12:15,943 --> 00:12:19,905
Sir Marcus, looks like
you're losing your edge.

180
00:12:20,656 --> 00:12:21,907
[Azuelo, in English]
Operations terminated!

181
00:12:22,491 --> 00:12:23,993
- [in English] Return to base! Everybody!
- [officer 1] Yes, sir!

182
00:12:24,076 --> 00:12:25,202
[all, in English] Yes, sir!

183
00:12:31,208 --> 00:12:36,338
[stirring music playing]

184
00:12:36,422 --> 00:12:38,549
[van engine starting]

185
00:12:42,553 --> 00:12:47,850
[car engine starting]

186
00:12:55,983 --> 00:12:57,109
[car door clicks open]

187
00:12:59,278 --> 00:13:03,240
[grim music playing]

188
00:13:05,868 --> 00:13:07,244
[Azuelo] Diez, Yambao!

189
00:13:07,328 --> 00:13:09,663
- [officer 2] Sir.
- Listen. You're on gate duty.

190
00:13:10,664 --> 00:13:12,166
- Delima!
- [Delima] Sir!

191
00:13:12,249 --> 00:13:14,502
- Orendo!
- Sir.

192
00:13:14,585 --> 00:13:18,506
You'll be on roving duty.
Keep a close eye on the perimeter.

193
00:13:18,589 --> 00:13:23,552
Be sure to report any unusual movements
as soon as possible.

194
00:13:23,636 --> 00:13:24,637
[in English] Understood?

195
00:13:24,720 --> 00:13:25,846
[officers in unison] Yes, sir!

196
00:13:27,223 --> 00:13:28,140
[Azuelo] Let's go.

197
00:13:28,224 --> 00:13:30,976
[van engine starting]

198
00:13:34,813 --> 00:13:36,941
[suspenseful music playing]

199
00:13:37,024 --> 00:13:38,192
[van door clicks shut]

200
00:13:40,653 --> 00:13:42,613
They weren't able to find Father!

201
00:13:46,367 --> 00:13:50,496
[tense music playing]

202
00:14:02,550 --> 00:14:05,469
[Azuelo] You gave me your word,
Agent Reyes!

203
00:14:06,220 --> 00:14:09,848
- You told me that Datu Rahman was there.
- [suspenseful music playing]

204
00:14:09,932 --> 00:14:11,725
But what did we find?

205
00:14:12,351 --> 00:14:13,644
Dust!

206
00:14:14,353 --> 00:14:15,229
[sighs]

207
00:14:15,312 --> 00:14:18,649
Sir. It's just
that I haven't found him yet.

208
00:14:19,233 --> 00:14:22,403
But I'm certain that they didn't move
the subject out of the Zylverix building.

209
00:14:22,486 --> 00:14:23,946
Datu Rahman is still in there!

210
00:14:24,029 --> 00:14:25,656
[in English] That's ridiculous!

211
00:14:26,448 --> 00:14:30,578
We've turned the building
upside down twice,

212
00:14:30,661 --> 00:14:32,496
but it's still negative!

213
00:14:32,580 --> 00:14:36,584
[in English] You've wasted
the purest time and resources!

214
00:14:37,167 --> 00:14:42,882
I committed four officers
to guard a ghost building because of you!

215
00:14:44,174 --> 00:14:46,677
This is why we've become a laughing stock!

216
00:14:46,760 --> 00:14:47,845
[smacks]

217
00:14:50,097 --> 00:14:51,140
Sir.

218
00:14:52,057 --> 00:14:54,143
I am positive
that I will find Datu Rahman.

219
00:14:54,226 --> 00:14:55,561
[in English] Just give me more time.

220
00:14:58,147 --> 00:15:02,818
[in English] I'm giving you
until 0200 hours.

221
00:15:02,902 --> 00:15:07,615
If you still come up empty-handed,
abort the operation,

222
00:15:07,698 --> 00:15:09,366
let go of that lead.

223
00:15:12,077 --> 00:15:13,162
[in English] Yes, sir.

224
00:15:18,918 --> 00:15:20,085
[door clicks shut]

225
00:15:22,004 --> 00:15:24,423
Marcus. Are you okay?

226
00:15:25,132 --> 00:15:26,550
[sighs] I'm fine.

227
00:15:27,051 --> 00:15:28,302
Don't be too hard on yourself.

228
00:15:28,385 --> 00:15:30,262
[in English] We followed protocol.

229
00:15:30,346 --> 00:15:33,432
We'll track the subject down eventually.
Maybe we just need new intel.

230
00:15:35,059 --> 00:15:35,976
Maybe.

231
00:15:37,645 --> 00:15:39,063
Thank you, Lara.

232
00:15:42,733 --> 00:15:43,984
[door thuds]

233
00:15:48,405 --> 00:15:52,117
[intriguing music playing]

234
00:15:56,705 --> 00:15:58,123
[officer] Sir Marcus.

235
00:15:58,207 --> 00:16:01,710
Negative on the other wing.
Unit 1 has also cleared the storage area.

236
00:16:02,711 --> 00:16:04,171
[sighs]

237
00:16:04,838 --> 00:16:06,298
If I'm right,

238
00:16:07,925 --> 00:16:10,052
the elevator should be here.

239
00:16:11,971 --> 00:16:13,681
But why isn't it here?

240
00:16:13,764 --> 00:16:18,477
[intriguing music continues]

241
00:16:21,438 --> 00:16:24,108
The elevator isn't on the blueprint.

242
00:16:26,568 --> 00:16:28,821
It's an off-the-books modification.

243
00:16:31,198 --> 00:16:37,997
[music turns stirring]

244
00:16:38,080 --> 00:16:39,123
[vehicle honking]

245
00:16:42,876 --> 00:16:48,048
[tense music playing]

246
00:16:52,261 --> 00:16:54,263
Jardin, have you seen Agent Reyes?

247
00:16:54,346 --> 00:16:56,473
Oh, yes, ma'am. He left in a hurry.

248
00:16:56,557 --> 00:16:58,434
He must've gone somewhere important.

249
00:17:05,774 --> 00:17:07,818
[line ringing]

250
00:17:08,986 --> 00:17:10,279
[mutters]

251
00:17:11,905 --> 00:17:13,949
[mutters, sighs]

252
00:17:16,243 --> 00:17:18,454
- [disconnect beeping]
- [sighs sharply]

253
00:17:20,080 --> 00:17:21,749
[line ringing]

254
00:17:22,332 --> 00:17:24,585
Get Datu Rahman out of there now!

255
00:17:25,961 --> 00:17:27,004
[cell phone thuds]

256
00:17:27,713 --> 00:17:31,550
[breathing heavily]

257
00:17:36,430 --> 00:17:38,307
- Sir!
- Good evening, Sir Marcus.

258
00:17:38,390 --> 00:17:40,225
[Yambao] I've already removed
the CCTV cameras.

259
00:17:44,396 --> 00:17:49,234
[unsettling music playing]

260
00:18:11,757 --> 00:18:12,633
Yambao.

261
00:18:13,884 --> 00:18:16,178
There are CCTV cameras
at the building entrance.

262
00:18:16,804 --> 00:18:19,681
Remove them. Make sure no one sees you.

263
00:18:20,224 --> 00:18:22,059
Stay out of sight.

264
00:18:23,477 --> 00:18:25,646
Good job. Thank you.

265
00:18:28,524 --> 00:18:29,942
[Yambao] Open the gate!

266
00:18:31,193 --> 00:18:33,112
- Escort Sir Marcus. Hurry up.
- [chains clattering]

267
00:18:33,195 --> 00:18:34,279
[officer] Okay, sir.

268
00:18:35,531 --> 00:18:39,660
[suspenseful music playing]

269
00:19:03,392 --> 00:19:07,146
[suspenseful music continues]

270
00:19:21,118 --> 00:19:23,704
[Marcus] <i>If this elevator isn't</i>
<i>in the original blueprint,</i>

271
00:19:24,788 --> 00:19:26,999
<i>this could be a ghost shaft.</i>

272
00:19:28,250 --> 00:19:30,586
<i>They could be hiding something here.</i>

273
00:19:30,669 --> 00:19:35,883
[suspenseful music continues, ends]

274
00:19:35,966 --> 00:19:39,011
[stirring music playing]

275
00:19:39,720 --> 00:19:40,929
[elevator dings]

276
00:19:41,722 --> 00:19:47,895
[whirring sound]

277
00:19:54,443 --> 00:19:58,822
[stirring music continues]

278
00:20:10,375 --> 00:20:11,501
[man grunts]

279
00:20:16,048 --> 00:20:18,926
[stirring music continues]

280
00:20:19,009 --> 00:20:19,968
[heaving]

281
00:20:24,097 --> 00:20:25,390
[elevator dings]

282
00:20:27,267 --> 00:20:31,688
[music intensifies]

283
00:20:47,496 --> 00:20:49,373
[metal rod clatters]

284
00:20:54,503 --> 00:20:56,380
[padlock clatters]

285
00:20:56,463 --> 00:21:01,885
[tense music continues]

286
00:21:04,680 --> 00:21:05,889
Psst!

287
00:21:06,807 --> 00:21:08,267
[grunting]

288
00:21:08,350 --> 00:21:09,851
- [groans]
- [shouts]

289
00:21:11,228 --> 00:21:14,940
[both grunting]

290
00:21:15,023 --> 00:21:18,360
[man grunts]

291
00:21:18,443 --> 00:21:25,367
[tense music continues]

292
00:21:25,450 --> 00:21:27,202
[grunting and groaning]

293
00:21:31,290 --> 00:21:33,250
[grunting and groaning]

294
00:21:33,333 --> 00:21:35,711
- [bones snap]
- [man screams]

295
00:21:42,175 --> 00:21:43,677
- [man] No!
- Take me to Datu Rahman.

296
00:21:43,760 --> 00:21:45,137
[man grunts]

297
00:21:45,220 --> 00:21:50,309
[tense music swells]

298
00:21:56,356 --> 00:21:58,150
[Marcus] <i>Who are you, Datu Rahman?</i>

299
00:21:58,233 --> 00:22:01,528
<i>Why are they ready to take</i>
<i>so many lives just for you?</i>

300
00:22:01,611 --> 00:22:04,489
[Jalil] <i>I need to uncover the truth</i>
<i>before they kill me.</i>

301
00:22:05,574 --> 00:22:06,992
[Lara] <i>What happened?</i>

302
00:22:07,075 --> 00:22:08,660
[sharp inhale] <i>They've found</i>
<i>the CCTV cameras.</i>

303
00:22:15,042 --> 00:22:18,837
[suspenseful music playing]

304
00:22:18,920 --> 00:22:21,673
- [kick lands]
- [gunshots]

305
00:22:21,757 --> 00:22:23,342
Reyes, Angeles, what the hell happened?!

306
00:22:25,135 --> 00:22:26,720
[Marcus] <i>My hunch was right.</i>

307
00:22:26,803 --> 00:22:28,638
This is where they brought Datu Rahman.

308
00:22:28,722 --> 00:22:29,973
It looks like they just moved him.

309
00:22:30,057 --> 00:22:32,893
Who took him, and where did they go?

310
00:22:34,478 --> 00:22:39,441
Keep an eye out for any concealed keyway
or suspicious-looking access panel.

311
00:22:39,524 --> 00:22:40,942
[Azuelo] <i>How did this happen, Agent Reyes?</i>

312
00:22:41,026 --> 00:22:43,653
<i>You said you would find Datu Rahman,</i>

313
00:22:43,737 --> 00:22:46,323
<i>but how did he manage to evade you again?</i>

314
00:22:46,406 --> 00:22:49,826
[reporter] <i>Why did it end in a shootout?</i>
<i>Was the intel wrong?</i>

315
00:22:49,910 --> 00:22:51,912
<i>Has Datu Rahman escaped once again?</i>

316
00:22:51,995 --> 00:22:53,830
Jalil is in that very building.

317
00:22:53,914 --> 00:22:55,040
What is he doing there?

318
00:22:55,123 --> 00:22:57,334
He believes Datu Rahman
is being held there.

319
00:22:57,417 --> 00:22:59,252
Oh! We must go there!

320
00:22:59,336 --> 00:23:00,504
Did something happen to Brother Jalil?

321
00:23:01,379 --> 00:23:02,756
[frustrated scream]

322
00:23:02,839 --> 00:23:04,091
How did this happen?!

323
00:23:04,174 --> 00:23:06,134
Who took you?! Who?!

324
00:23:07,511 --> 00:23:09,763
[suspenseful music playing]
